{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3522078,"name":"","username":"Hollisms","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/hollisms/{size}/110925_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-10T12:59:47.516Z","cooked":"<p>Hello <span class="abbreviation">CD<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Chief Delphi"></template></span>.</p>
<p>I have read lots of posts for this season about how to control elevators and arms.  One approach is with a state machine.  Our 2023 robot used this method and we are going to be using something similar this year.  I took our 2023 code and created a very generic <a href="https://github.com/hollisms/GraphCommandExample/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/Arm.java" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">example</a>.</p>
<p>The full example is here:<br>
<a href="https://github.com/hollisms/GraphCommandExample" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">https://github.com/hollisms/GraphCommandExample</a></p>
<p>The GraphCommand is here:<br>
<a href="https://github.com/hollisms/GraphCommandExample/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/util/GraphCommand/GraphCommand.java" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">src/main/java/frc/util/GraphCommand</a></p>
<p>Feel free to clone/fork and use as you like.  You just need to add the GraphCommand.java file into your project, if you choose to use it.</p>
<p>The intent is to create a Subsystem, create a GraphCommand and set it as the default command.  Then use it to send Commands to your other subsystems.  The example lays this out.  Additionally, in the sample project there is a <a href="https://github.com/hollisms/GraphCommandExample/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/arm.drawio.svg" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">picture</a> of the graph that was created using <a href="http://draw.io" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">draw.io</a>.  There is a <a href="http://draw.io" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">draw.io</a> plugin for vscode.</p>
<p>Additionally, here is a sample exerpt from our robot so you can see how it might look…</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">        Start = m_armGraph.new GraphCommandNode("Start",
                ArmController.getArmCommand(Degrees.of(0),
                        Meters.of(0),
                        Degrees.of(0)),
                null,
                null);
        BackAligment = m_armGraph.new GraphCommandNode("BackAlignment",
                ArmController.getArmCommand(Degrees.of(90),
                        Meters.of(0),
                        Degrees.of(-90))
                        .andThen(RobotContainer.m_armBase.getWaitUntilErrorLessThanCmd(Degrees.of(70.0)))
                        .andThen(RobotContainer.m_armExtension.getWaitUntilErrorLessThanCmd(Meters.of(0.5))),
                null,
                new PrintCommand("BackAlignment is done"));
</code></pre>
<p>In this sample code the method <code>ArmController.getArmCommand(x,y,z)</code> is a Command factory that configures the 3 degrees of freedom for our arm.  Each is implemented in its own subsystem.  The <code>.andThen()</code> conditions are used to specify when the transition to the state has been achieved.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2025-02-10T17:37:43.009Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":78,"reads":285,"readers_count":284,"score":567.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":491005,"topic_slug":"graphcommand-state-machine","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":4,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/hollisms/GraphCommandExample","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - hollisms/GraphCommandExample","clicks":31},{"url":"https://github.com/hollisms/GraphCommandExample/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/util/GraphCommand/GraphCommand.java","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GraphCommandExample/src/main/java/frc/util/GraphCommand/GraphCommand.java at main · hollisms/GraphCommandExample · GitHub","clicks":23},{"url":"https://github.com/hollisms/GraphCommandExample/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/arm.drawio.svg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"arm.drawio.svg","clicks":23},{"url":"https://github.com/hollisms/GraphCommandExample/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/Arm.java","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GraphCommandExample/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/Arm.java at main · hollisms/GraphCommandExample · GitHub","clicks":12},{"url":"http://draw.io","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Flowchart Maker & Online Diagram Software","clicks":8}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":fals