ASS Creator ","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3522754,"name":"","username":"Hollisms","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/hollisms/{size}/110925_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-10T22:14:31.219Z","cooked":"<p>Philosophically, I think triggers (event-driven architecture) are great for stimulus-response applications. I believe state machines are well-suited for process- or orchestration-based applications. There is a lot of overlap and gray area.</p>
<p>Practically, in my opinion, if you want your mechanism to proceed sequentially through a series of “set points” or “waypoints,” a state machine is better suited.</p>
